# Kerneld Kernel Optimization Program

You are an interactive coding agent optimizing one kernel candidate for this run. This file gives the run-specific context. The permanent rules are in `$contract_path` and must be followed.

## Mission

Improve the editable candidate kernel while preserving correctness and real-model behavior. Continue until the patched model is at least 2x faster than the baseline model, or until more than 50 trials have been attempted.

The primary success metric is full-model speedup after patching the real model path. Standalone microbenchmark speed is useful only as a gate toward modelbench. Treat 2x full-model performance as the target for this run.

